<article>
    <h1>Un&#xAD;cov&#xAD;er&#xAD;ing Sin&#xAD;ga&#xAD;pore again</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201220/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-20"><time>2020-12-20</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Pre-pan­demic, long week­ends used to mean lines at air­port check-in coun­ters as peo­ple flocked to neigh­bour­ing ci­ties such as Bangkok.</p>
    <p>Now, the new nor­mal is check­ing into a lo­cal ho­tel. Stay­cays have flour­ished this year, with many ho­tels and ser­viced apart­ments see­ing strong de­mand, es­pe­cially for the year-end school hol­i­days.</p>
    <p>Prop­er­ties have upped their game, part­ner­ing lo­cal at­trac­tions and tour op­er­a­tors to launch pack­ages.</p>
    <p>M Social and Or­chard Ho­tel, both man­aged by Mil­len­nium Ho­tels and Re­sorts, of­fer a “yacht-cation”, which in­cludes a half-day sail­ing and pic­nic lunch on top of a night’s stay at ei­ther ho­tel.</p>
    <p>Smaller ho­tels are no slouch ei­ther, work­ing with small busi­nesses and social en­ter­prises to cre­ate unique, hy­per-lo­cal ex­pe­ri­ences.</p>
    <p>For ex­am­ple, The Sul­tan, a bou­tique ho­tel in Kam­pong Glam, of­fers discounts on a batik work­shop and an In­stawalk for stay­ca­tion guests.</p>
    <p>And co-liv­ing ho­tel ST Sig­na­ture Jalan Be­sar holds minia­ture clay art work­shops – where even the clum­si­est fin­gers can pro­duce dainty morsels of as­sorted kueh – run by social en­ter­prise Tin­kle Arts.</p>
    <p>Fans of un­con­ven­tional quar­ters can bed down in a ship­ping con­tainer ho­tel or glamp­ing tent in Jewel Changi Air­port.</p>
    <p>Even with­out go­ing on a stay­ca­tion, a sense of ex­plo­ration is well and truly alive. Lo­cal at­trac­tions, such as Sen­tosa’s ca­ble car line, see long queues on week­ends and Lazarus Is­land’s “se­cret beach” has never seen so much ac­tion.</p>
    <p>With its world-class ho­tels and at­trac­tions, Sin­ga­pore has long topped travel des­ti­na­tion lists, es­pe­cially among trav­ellers in Asia.</p>
    <p>For lo­cals, 2020 was the year Sin­ga­pore­ans learnt to ap­pre­ci­ate their back­yard anew.</p>
    <p>Clara Lock</p>

